HEADWORD: Caliduct
<hw>Cal"i*duct</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Caloriduct</er>.]</ety> <def>A pipe or duct used to convey hot air
or steam.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Subterranean <qex>caliducts</qex> have been introduced.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

